text.__SUMMARY__: Shorea roxburghii is a species of tree in the family Dipterocarpaceae. It is native to Cambodia, India, Laos, Malaysia, Burma, Thailand, and Vietnam.
text.Common names:
Malay: temak, a name it sometimes shares with Shorea hypochra
Thai: พยอม, transliterated phayom
Vietnamese: Sến đỏ
text.References in place names:
Ban Dongphayom (บ้านดงพยอม) in Thailand, literally Shorea Roxburghii Forest Village
